def minPath(grid, k):
    n = len(grid)
    start = min((grid[i][j], i, j) for i in range(n) for j in range(n))[1:]
    path = [grid[start[0]][start[1]]]
    visited = set([start])
    
    while len(path) < k:
        x, y = start
        neighbors = [(x+1, y), (x-1, y), (x, y+1), (x, y-1)]
        next_cell = min((grid[i][j], i, j) for i, j in neighbors if 0 <= i < n and 0 <= j < n and (i, j) not in visited)[1:]
        path.append(grid[next_cell[0]][next_cell[1]])
        visited.add(next_cell)
        start = next_cell
    
    return path
